HEADWORD: Isonephelic
<hw>I`so*ne*phel"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a cloud.]</ety> <fld>(Phys. Geog.)</fld>
<def>Having, or indicating, an equal amount of cloudiness for a given
period; <as>as, <ex>isonephelic</ex> regions; an <ex>isonephelic</ex>
line.</as></def>⟦br⟧
